value.value: The apodeme that arises ventromedially form the metapectus, extends towards the metapleural apodeme and corresponds to the site of origin of metacoxal and metatrochanteral muscles.
The furcal pit that is located in the metathorax.
The metacoxal muscle that originates from the metafurca and inserts on the posterior margin of the metacoxa.
The metatrochanteral muscle that arises from the metafurca and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.
The second abdominal sternal muscle that arises from the metafurca and inserts on abdominal sternum 2.
The median process on the metascutellum.
The area that is concave, and is delimited medially by the metascutellum, laterally by the supraalar area and posteriorly by the metascutellar arm.
The sulcus that extends along the anterior margin of the fused metanotum and abdominal tergum 1 and delimit an anterior narrow, usually differently sculptured area.
The metatrochanteral muscle that originates from the humeral sclerite and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.
The alinotum that is located in the metathorax, is connected with the mesoscutellum and the mesopostnotum anteriorly and the acrotergite of the first abdominal tergum posteromedially.

The sclerite that is connected anteriorly with the mesopectus dorsally with the metanotum, the metabasalare, second axillary sclerite of the hind wing and the metasubalare and articulates with the metacoxae and the metasoma.
The area that is located anteriorly of the metapleural sulcus and ridge.
The phragma that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesophragmo-metaphragmal and metaphragmo-second abdominal tergal muscles.
The pleural apodeme that is connected with the metafurca.
The area that is located anterodorsally on the metapleuron.

The carina that delimits the metapleuron dorsally from the propodeum, extends from just ventral of the metapleural arm to the metacoxal articulation and passes anteroventral to the propodeal spiracle.
The carina that delimits posteriorly the metapleural triangle.
The epicoxal sulcus that extends anteriorly along and close to the metapleural epicoxal carina.
The pleural pit that is corresponds to the metapleural apodeme.
The pleural ridge that corresponds to the metapleural sulcus.
The line that corresponds with the metapleural ridge.
The area that is located anteroventrally on the metapectus, is delimited ventrally by the ventral carina of the metapleuron and is triangular.
The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metabasalare.
The metanotal muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metanotum.
The metasubalare muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metasubalare.
The metatrochanteral muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.

label.value: metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle

value.value: The hind wing third axillary muscle that originates from the metapleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of the hind wing.
The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located laterally of the metadiscrimen.
The area that is elevated and extends along the posterior margin of the metanotum from the metascutellum to the supraalar area.
The carina that delimits laterally the metascutellum.
The area that is located posteromedially on the metanotum, is delimited laterally by the metanotal trough and corresponds to the reservoir of the dorsal vessel.
The tagma that is connected anteriorly to the metapectal-propodeal complex at the propodeal foramen and consists of abdominal segments.
The acetabulum that is concave, surrounds the nucha and accommodates the base of the metasoma.
The eusternum that is located in the metathorax.
The subalare that is located in the metathorax.
The thoracic segment that is located between the mesothorax and the first abdominal tergum and is delimited by the metanotum and the metapectus.
The tibia that is located on the hind leg.
The epimeron that is located on the metapleuron and is located posteriorly of the metapleural sulcus.
The scrobe that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus and accommodates the mesocoxa.
The episternum that is located anteroventrally of the metapleural sulcus.
The coxa that is located on the mid leg.
The leg that is located on the mesothorax.
The depression that is located posteromedially on the mesoscutum.
The joint that is composed of two sclerites that are connected with one articulation.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the labrum, epipharyngeal wall, hypopharyngeal wall (including the sitophore), mandibles, maxillae, labium and conjunctivae connecting them.
The sensillum that corresponds to a multiporous plate.
The portion of tissue that is composed of contractile fibers.

label.value: muscle bearing process of the metanotum

value.value: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of insertions of the lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscles.
The intrinsic leg muscle that originates within the tibia and femur and has a long tendon that inserts through the terminal tarsomere onto the unguitractor.
The area that is located posteroventrally on the pronotum and corresponds to the site of origin of first flexor of the fore wing muscle.
